                <h3>What the price depends on</h3> <br>
                <p>
                    <b class="add-number">1</b> <b>Number of subscribers</b> <br>
                    The more readers, the more reach of the audience and, respectively, the higher advertising cost (unless this are live people, not bots)
                </p>
                <p>
                    <b class="add-number">2</b> <b>Blogger's self-esteem</b> <br>
                    You can simply find two similar accounts with the same number of subscribers, but the owner of
                    one will want $200, and the other $500
                </p>
                <p>
                    <b class="add-number">3</b> <b>Indicators of involvement</b> <br>
                    To calculate the percentage of experience, add the number of likes and comments
                    on the page and divide this amount by the number of blogger posts (you can choose only last posts).
                    In a good account the number of comments equals 8-10% of the number of likes.
                    This comments must be alive and on the topic, and also, contain at least 4 words.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <b class="add-number">4</b> <b>Advertising type and its duration</b> <br>
                    You can order different types of ad: instagram post, story; instagram live; video, photo; review, recommendation and so more.
                    Some formats will be expensive, others will be cheaper.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <b class="text-primary">*</b>Choosing a blogger for advertising, you should be careful.
                    Many offers may be unfavorable due to the count of bots in subscribers.
                </p>
